mento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2023-07-18\" src=\"ISic003115_right-thumb.jpg\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic003115_rear_tiled.tif\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2023-07-18\" src=\"ISic003115_rear_tiled-thumb.tif\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic003115_rear.jpg\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2023-07-18\" src=\"ISic003115_rear-thumb.jpg\">\u003C/a>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"apparatus\">\u003Ch4>Apparatus criticus\u003C/h4>\u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan>  \u003Cspan>Text of Brugnone2024, checked against photograph\u003C/span>  \u003C/span>; \u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"2\">2: \u003Cspan>Brugnone: alternatively Ποπλείο[ς]\u003C/span>  \u003C/span>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"translation\">\u003Ch2> translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">  \u003C/p>\u003Cp>Damatrios son of Popleios, blessed one, rejoice!\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"commentary\">\u003Ch2>commentary\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>The formula μακαρῖτα χαῖρε is found in another funerary epitaph at Lilybaeum, \u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic003660\" target=\"_blank\">ISic003660\u003C/a>. The second name, Popleios (i.e. Latin Publius) could either be a patronymic, or else the adoption of a Latin name as a second name, as attested in other Sicilian cases (Cic. Verr. 2.4.35, 2.5.16).\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"bibliography\">\u003Ch2>bibliography\u003C/h2>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli> 26.1075 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000796\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000796\u003C/a>  \u003C/li>\u003Cli> Manni Piraino 1976 213-215 no.1 